Description
Appointment
This class creates Appointment objects that allow for appoinment display across the application.

A class used for company contacts in the application.
Country
Models countries in the database to allow filtering on several controllers.
CountryRecord

A class used to display existing customers across the application.
CustomerAddController
Controls the form responsible for adding new customers.
CustomerUpdateController
Controls the form responsible for updating existing customers.
CustomerValidator
Validates input for the add and update controllers for customer data entry.
DBConnector
Creates connections to the MySQL database across the application.
DisplayContacts
Provides a container for contact display in several combo boxes in add/update forms.
DisplayLocations
Models locations such as country and division for use in combo box display across the application.
DisplayMinutes
Creates a collection of Minute objects formatted for display.
Division
An extension of the Location class used to model first level divisions from the database.
Location
Allows the creation of classes used to model different types of locations such as Country and Division.
LogInController
Controls the form responsible for logging in authorized users.
LogInLogger
Provides methods to record log-in successes and failures to a local text file.

Minute

MonthTypeRecord
Models the record used in the report displaying amount of appointments by month and type.

Person
An abstract class generally used to model people associated with the company appointments.
Query

Models the schedule contained in the MySQL database.
